**Describe the bug**
Attempting to display a string containing a `\t` in a table cell causes a DocumentDrawingException. [This](https://www.fileformat.info/info/unicode/font/arial/list.htm) source says that the Arial font should support the `\t` character. The exception thrown is the following: 

```
QuestPDF.Drawing.Exceptions.DocumentDrawingException: Could not find an appropriate font fallback for glyph: U-0009 '\t'. Font families available on current environment that contain this glyph: Microsoft PhagsPa. Possible solutions: 1) Use one of the listed fonts as the primary font in your document. 2) Configure the fallback TextStyle using the 'TextStyle.Fallback' method with one of the listed fonts.
```

Setting the fallback font to `Microsoft PhagsPa` does stop the exception, but that's a font for typing Mongolian characters and isn't really a solution since Arial should support this character.

**To Reproduce**

I set the default page font to Arial in the `Compose()` method like this: 

```
public void Compose (IDocumentContainer container)
        {
            container
                .Page(page =>
                {
                    page.DefaultTextStyle(x => x
                        .FontFamily(Fonts.Arial));

                    // Drawing the page content, table with problem is drawn in ComposeContent()
                    page.Header().ShowOnce().Element(ComposeHeader);
                    page.Content().Element(ComposeContent);
                    page.Footer().Element(ComposeFooter);
                });
        }
```

Then I have a table cell that looks like this: 

```
table.Cell().Element(ContentCellStyle).AlignCenter().Text(item.theProblemString);
```

```
static IContainer ContentCellStyle(IContainer container) {
    return container.DefaultTextStyle(text => text.FontSize(8)).PaddingVertical(1);
}
```

`item.theProblemString` is a string property of my class instance that contains a `\t` character.

**Expected behavior**
An exception should not be thrown when a `\t` character appears in a string while the Arial font is used.

